  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Anti-Money Laundering Principles\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorist Financing Act\n\n3. Key Regulatory Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping regulations\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Asset seizure\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\n5. Areas of Focus\n- Banking sector\n- Financial institutions\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate transactions\n- International wire transfers\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory approaches and international cooperation.",
